# UI/UX & Branding Governance — Blind Teknologis Website

Tyson holds final approval over all user-facing design decisions on this site. This is the
one part of the project he wants to be personally involved in — do not ship a design
decision without his sign-off, even if the change looks small.

## Design Review Standard

- Always present one primary recommendation plus at least two clearly, visibly different
  alternatives, with a tradeoff explanation for each.
- Never present multiple options that are near-identical variants of each other unless
  Tyson explicitly asked for variations on one specific concept.
- Always provide a visual preview (screenshot of the actual rendered page/component, or a
  generated concept image) for any meaningful design decision — never describe a design
  only in prose. Use a real browser screenshot of the running `npm run dev` site whenever
  the component already exists; use image generation only for pre-implementation concept
  exploration.

## Logo Rules (Permanent)

The approved Blind Teknologis logo must be preserved exactly.

- **Allowed changes:** container shape, background, padding, placement, scale,
  border-radius.
- **Not allowed:** redrawing, font changes, altering lettering, simplifying, or text
  replacement.
- Current assets: `public/logo.png` (black/red, for light backgrounds — header) and
  `public/logo-on-dark.png` (white/red, for dark backgrounds — footer). Do not introduce a
  third variant without checking these two first.
- If the current export looks soft at retina sizes, re-export at higher resolution
  (600×180 / 900×270) — do not upscale the existing file or redraw the mark.

## Current Approved Design Direction

- **Blind Teknologis (company, this site):** premium, enterprise, modern, minimal,
  high-end SaaS/industrial-equipment feel (think Palantir/Stripe-adjacent, not "AI
  startup" or "racing/gaming"). Palette: charcoal/near-black background, white primary
  text, metallic red accent used sparingly — roughly a 90% neutral / 10% red accent ratio.
  Do not let red dominate the composition.
- **TekBox (product, referenced within this site):** may diverge from the parent palette
  (dark navy + orange has been explored); industrial/diagnostic-tool visual motif
  ("everything you need is in here") is the strongest validated concept so far. TekBox is
  referenced as the product Blind Teknologis builds — do not present it as the public
  company brand.
- Layout convention on this site: alternating white / dark-inset content bands, all
  content constrained to the same left/right margin (`.section-shell` in
  `src/app/globals.css`) across hero, feature bands, and footer — keep new sections
  consistent with this rhythm unless Tyson explicitly asks to break it.
- Never claim an integration exists that hasn't shipped (e.g. say "in development," not
  "supported"). Never name the underlying AI vendors/models in public-facing copy. Never
  use invented or unverified statistics in marketing copy. Never show a partner/integration
  logo wall with unverified or placeholder logos.

## Process

Before generating new UI/marketing visuals, briefly restate which of the above constraints
apply, then produce the multi-option comparison. Do not iterate on a single direction for
many small rounds when a design decision is genuinely undecided — surface the distinct
options up front instead.

For hands-on visual concept generation (new page layouts, hero treatments, brand
explorations for web, app, or any other surface), delegate to the UI/UX Designer agent —
see `.cursor/agents/ui-ux-designer.md`.
